It's fine to keep this as is, but I ([and many other people](https://softwareengineering.stackexchange.com/questions/18454/should-i-return-from-a-function-early-or-use-an-if-statement)) usually recommend returning early to make the code easier to read. 

So here you could do

```
if (!this->ogreEntity->hasSkeleton())
  return;
```

and 

```
if (!skel->hasBone(pair.first))
  continue;
```
